e narrow headlight and lower running lights shine in the gloom. The car drives through a wet industrial or city street, surrounded by dark buildings and reflective pavement. Fine-print legal text appears along the bottom, too small to read clearly.\n\nThe red sedan advances toward the viewer through standing water. Its headlights and small lower lights reflect on the slick road surface. Spray rises around the tires as it moves, and the surrounding buildings look gray, hard-edged, and damp. The car then passes through a narrow street or alley lined with tall building walls, its rear red light bar glowing as it recedes into the rain.\n\nThe Charger swings through the wet roadway, sending water outward from its tires. White on-screen text appears at the lower left reading “DODGE CHARGER.” The car’s front is broad and low, with a black grille, bright headlights, and three small rectangular lower lights on each side. The red body contrasts sharply with the blue-gray rain and mist.\n\nFrom above, the red car continues across the dark, reflective street. It looks small against the wide, wet pavement, leaving a trail of spray behind it. A closer front view follows, with the right headlight glaring brightly through rain and mist. Centered over the car’s black grille, white text appears: “DOMESTIC.” Fine-print text remains faint along the bottom.\n\nThe word “DOMESTIC.” stays on screen as the car’s front fills the view, its lights bright and the grille dark. Rain and road spray partially veil the red bodywork. The text then expands to “DOMESTIC. NOT DOMESTICATED.” in white capital letters across the center-left of the screen, while the Charger moves past on the right side, mostly seen as a dark red blur through the rain.",
